SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1038
By Roberts
A RESOLUTION to designate Miss Tennessee as an official
ambassador for the State of Tennessee during
her reign.
WHEREAS, this year, 2026, marks America's 250th anniversary, and the Miss America
pageant, established in 1921 in Atlantic City, New Jersey, has made the winner, the newly
crowned Miss America, an icon in American history for over 100 years; and
WHEREAS, in the State of Tennessee, the Miss Tennessee Organization, affiliated with
the Miss America Opportunity, annually crowns the winner who then proudly represents the
Volunteer State in the official Miss America pageant; and
WHEREAS, the winner of the Miss Tennessee pageant strives to improve the quality of
life for her fellow citizens while bringing beauty, grace, and purpose to all their endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it would be a tremendous asset for the State of Tennessee to designate the
annual winner of the Miss Tennessee pageant as an official ambassador for the State of
Tennessee during her one-year reign, serving strictly in an honorary and volunteer capacity; and
WHEREAS, as an official ambassador for the State of Tennessee, Miss Tennessee
could advance goodwill, civic engagement, volunteer service, and the State's interests at official
and community events; and
WHEREAS, she could also promote Tennessee's communities, culture, history, tourism,
and public initiatives while encouraging volunteerism, community service, and goodwill across
the Volunteer State; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby designate Miss Tennessee, the individual
